sourcesContent:
import { Project, Skill, Experience, Education } from '../types';

export const personalInfo = {
  name: "Conor Van Bibber",
  title: "Electrical Engineer",
  subtitle: "RF/Microwave Engineer & Hardware Designer",
  email: "conorvanbibber@gmail.com",
  phone: "+1 (XXX) XXX-XXXX", // Update with actual phone
  location: "Berkeley, CA",
  linkedin: "https://linkedin.com/in/conor-van-bibber",
  github: "https://github.com/cvanbibber",
  website: "https://cvanbibber.github.io",
  bio: "Passionate electrical engineer specializing in RF/microwave design, antenna systems, and electromagnetic simulation. Experienced in both hardware design and software development with a focus on creating innovative solutions for complex engineering challenges."
};

export const skills: Skill[] = [
  // Programming
  { name: "Python", category: "programming", icon: "/skills/python.png" },
  { name: "C++", category: "programming", icon: "/skills/c++.png" },
  { name: "MATLAB", category: "programming", icon: "/skills/matlab.png" },
  
  // Hardware Design
  { name: "Altium Designer", category: "hardware", icon: "/skills/altium.png" },
  { name: "KiCad", category: "hardware", icon: "/skills/kicad.png" },
  
  // CAD/Mechanical
  { name: "SolidWorks", category: "software", icon: "/skills/solidworks.png" },
  { name: "Fusion 360", category: "software", icon: "/skills/fusion.png" },
  
  // Analysis Software
  { name: "ANSYS HFSS", category: "analysis", icon: "/skills/hfss.png" },
  { name: "ANSYS Maxwell", category: "analysis", icon: "/skills/maxwell.png" },
  { name: "ANSYS Fluent", category: "analysis", icon: "/skills/ansysfluent.png" },
  { name: "OpenFOAM", category: "analysis", icon: "/skills/openfoam.png" },
  
  // Manufacturing
  { name: "3D Printing", category: "hardware", icon: "/skills/3dprint.png" },
  { name: "CNC Machining", category: "hardware", icon: "/skills/cnc.png" },
  { name: "Laser Cutting", category: "hardware", icon: "/skills/lasercut.png" },
  { name: "Lathe Operation", category: "hardware", icon: "/skills/lathe.png" }
];

export const experiences: Experience[] = [
  {
    id: "exp-1",
    title: "RF Engineer Intern",
    company: "Tech Company", // Update with actual company
    location: "San Francisco, CA",
    startDate: "2023-06",
    endDate: "2023-08",
    description: [
      "Designed and simulated antenna arrays for 5G applications using ANSYS HFSS",
      "Developed Python scripts for automated electromagnetic analysis and optimization",
      "Collaborated with cross-functional teams to integrate RF solutions into product designs",
      "Performed measurements and validation of prototype antenna systems"
    ],
    technologies: ["ANSYS HFSS", "Python", "RF Design", "Antenna Arrays", "5G"]
  },
  // Add more experiences as needed
];

export const education: Education[] = [
  {
    id: "edu-1",
    degree: "Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering",
    institution: "University of California, Berkeley",
    location: "Berkeley, CA",
    startDate: "2020-08",
    endDate: "2024-05", // Update as needed
    gpa: "3.8/4.0", // Update with actual GPA
    achievements: [
      "Dean's List (multiple semesters)",
      "IEEE Student Member",
      "Senior Design Project: [Project Name]",
      "Relevant Coursework: Electromagnetics, RF Circuits, Antenna Theory, Signal Processing"
    ]
  }
];

export const projects: Project[] = [
  {
    id: "muon-detector",
    title: "Muon Detector System",
    description: "Advanced particle detection system using electromagnetic simulation and custom electronics for high-energy physics research",
    longDescription: "Designed and built a sophisticated muon detection system for physics research applications. The project involved extensive electromagnetic simulation using ANSYS HFSS to optimize detector geometry, custom PCB design for signal processing, and mechanical integration. The system successfully detects cosmic ray muons with high precision and provides real-time data analysis capabilities.",
    technologies: ["ANSYS HFSS", "PCB Design", "C++", "Python", "Signal Processing", "High-Energy Physics"],
    images: ["/static/media/muon2.7d3374d3.png", "/static/media/layout.2d74e840.png"],
    featured: true,
    category: "research",
    date: "2023-12",
    status: "completed",
    demoUrl: "",
    githubUrl: ""
  },
  {
    id: "hope-satellite",
    title: "HOPE Satellite Project",
    description: "Aerospace electronics and control systems for Berkeley's satellite program with advanced communication systems",
    longDescription: "Led the electronics and control systems development for Berkeley's HOPE satellite project. Designed high-frequency communication systems, power management circuits, and attitude control electronics. The project involved extensive RF simulation, PCB design for space applications, and integration with mechanical systems. Successfully passed all testing phases and deployment readiness assessments.",
    technologies: ["RF Design", "Altium Designer", "Aerospace Electronics", "ANSYS HFSS", "Power Management", "Embedded Systems"],
    images: ["/static/media/HOPEFRONT.6cf372d4.png", "/static/media/HOPE_BACK.d0ad02cc.png"],
    featured: true,
    category: "hardware",
    date: "2023-09",
    status: "completed"
  },
  {
    id: "advanced-pcb-designs",
    title: "Advanced PCB Designs",
    description: "High-frequency and mixed-signal circuit boards for various engineering applications",
    longDescription: "Collection of advanced PCB designs featuring high-frequency circuits, mixed-signal processing, and power electronics. Projects include multi-layer boards with controlled impedance, advanced routing techniques, and thermal management. Each design underwent extensive simulation and testing to ensure signal integrity and electromagnetic compatibility.",
    technologies: ["Altium Designer", "KiCAD", "High-Frequency Design", "Signal Integrity", "EMI/EMC", "Thermal Analysis"],
    images: ["/static/media/pcb.9c6b494a.png", "/static/media/layout.2d74e840.png"],
    featured: true,
    category: "hardware",
    date: "2023-11",
    status: "completed"
  },
  {
    id: "needex-platform",
    title: "Needex Platform",
    description: "Integrated mechatronics platform combining mechanical design, electronics, and software for automated systems",
    longDescription: "Developed a comprehensive mechatronics platform that integrates mechanical design, electronics, and software control. The project features custom mechanical components designed using SolidWorks with generative design principles, advanced control electronics, and real-time software systems. The platform demonstrates the seamless integration of mechanical, electrical, and computational systems.",
    technologies: ["SolidWorks", "Generative Design", "Embedded Systems", "Real-time Control", "Mechatronics Integration"],
    images: ["/static/media/Needex.f0ab30a3.png", "/static/media/newmain.43a51081.png"],
    featured: true,
    category: "cad",
    date: "2023-08",
    status: "completed"
  },
  {
    id: "cad-optimization",
    title: "CAD Design Optimization",
    description: "Advanced CAD projects utilizing generative design and topology optimization for lightweight structures",
    longDescription: "Series of advanced CAD projects focusing on generative design and topology optimization. Used AI-powered design tools including Fusion 360's generative design and Hyperganic's algorithmic design to create optimized structures. Projects include lightweight aerospace components, heat sink optimization, and structural topology optimization with significant weight and performance improvements.",
    technologies: ["Fusion 360", "Generative Design", "Topology Optimization", "Hyperganic", "FEA", "Additive Manufacturing"],
    images: ["/static/media/cad.d4c3ac4a.png", "/static/media/test2.56042cff.png"],
    featured: false,
    category: "cad",
    date: "2023-06",
    status: "completed"
  },
  {
    id: "nuclear-engineering",
    title: "Nuclear Engineering Analysis",
    description: "Computational analysis and simulation for nuclear engineering applications using advanced numerical methods",
    longDescription: "Advanced computational analysis for nuclear engineering applications including reactor physics simulations, neutron transport calculations, and thermal-hydraulic analysis. The project utilized high-performance computing techniques and specialized nuclear engineering software to model complex physical phenomena and optimize system designs.",
    technologies: ["MATLAB", "Python", "Computational Physics", "Nuclear Engineering", "HPC", "Numerical Analysis"],
    images: ["/static/media/ne180hw1.7ef3a7c1.png"],
    featured: false,
    category: "research",
    date: "2023-05",
    status: "completed"
  },
  {
    id: "manufacturing-projects",
    title: "Advanced Manufacturing",
    description: "Precision manufacturing projects using CNC machining, 3D printing, and traditional machining techniques",
    longDescription: "Comprehensive manufacturing projects demonstrating expertise in both traditional and advanced manufacturing techniques. Projects include precision CNC machining of aerospace components, advanced 3D printing with multiple technologies (SLA, SLS, FDM), and traditional lathe/mill operations. Focus on achieving tight tolerances and superior surface finishes for critical applications.",
    technologies: ["CNC Machining", "3D Printing", "SolidWorks CAM", "Precision Manufacturing", "Quality Control"],
    images: ["/static/media/lathe.9f6a25fc.jpg"],
    featured: false,
    category: "hardware",
    date: "2023-04",
    status: "completed"
  }
];

export const featuredProjects = projects.filter(project => project.featured);
